theorem interior_inter_interior_right {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} :
    interior (A ∩ interior (B : Set X)) = interior (A ∩ B) := by
  apply le_antisymm
  · -- `⊆` : monotonicity of `interior`
    have hsubset : (A ∩ interior (B : Set X) : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro x hx
      exact ⟨hx.1, interior_subset hx.2⟩
    exact interior_mono hsubset
  · -- `⊇` : a point of `interior (A ∩ B)` is also in the RHS
    intro x hxInt
    -- From `x ∈ interior (A ∩ B)` obtain an open neighbourhood `V`.
    rcases mem_interior.1 hxInt with ⟨V, hVsub, hVopen, hxV⟩
    -- `x` is in the interior of `B`, hence there is an open `W`.
    have hxIntB : x ∈ interior (B : Set X) :=
      (interior_mono (Set.inter_subset_right : (A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ B)) hxInt
    rcases mem_interior.1 hxIntB with ⟨W, hWsub, hWopen, hxW⟩
    -- Intersect the two neighbourhoods.
    let U : Set X := V ∩ W
    have hUopen : IsOpen U := hVopen.inter hWopen
    have hxU : x ∈ U := ⟨hxV, hxW⟩
    -- `U` is contained in `A ∩ interior B`.
    have hUsub : (U : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ interior (B : Set X) := by
      intro y hy
      have hyV : y ∈ V := hy.1
      have hyW : y ∈ W := hy.2
      have hyA : y ∈ A := (hVsub hyV).1
      have hyIntB : y ∈ interior (B : Set X) := hWsub hyW
      exact ⟨hyA, hyIntB⟩
    -- Hence `x ∈ interior (A ∩ interior B)`.
    exact mem_interior.2 ⟨U, hUsub, hUopen, hxU⟩

theorem closure_inter_interior_subset_closure_inter' {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X]
    {A B : Set X} :
    closure (A : Set X) ∩ interior B ⊆ closure (A ∩ B) := by
  intro x hx
  rcases hx with ⟨hxClA, hxIntB⟩
  -- We will show `x ∈ closure (A ∩ B)` via the neighbourhood
  -- characterisation of the closure.
  have : x ∈ closure (A ∩ B : Set X) := by
    -- Reformulate membership in the closure.
    refine (mem_closure_iff).2 ?_
    intro U hUopen hxU
    -- Consider the open neighbourhood `U ∩ interior B` of `x`.
    have hVopen : IsOpen (U ∩ interior B) := hUopen.inter isOpen_interior
    have hxV : x ∈ U ∩ interior B := ⟨hxU, hxIntB⟩
    -- As `x ∈ closure A`, this neighbourhood meets `A`.
    have hNon : ((U ∩ interior B) ∩ (A : Set X)).Nonempty := by
      have h := (mem_closure_iff).1 hxClA
      simpa [Set.inter_assoc, Set.inter_left_comm, Set.inter_comm]
        using h (U ∩ interior B) hVopen hxV
    -- Extract a witness `y` in the intersection.
    rcases hNon with ⟨y, ⟨⟨hyU, hyIntB⟩, hyA⟩⟩
    -- `y` also lies in `B` since it is in `interior B`.
    have hyB : y ∈ B := interior_subset hyIntB
    exact ⟨y, ⟨hyU, ⟨hyA, hyB⟩⟩⟩
  exact this
